 precarious labour markets and neoliberalism. This book goes beyond the aggregated statistics to explore the lived experiences of older people attempting to make job transitions. Drawing on the voices of older workers in a diverse range of European countries, leading scholars explore job redeployment and job mobility, temporary employment, unemployment, employment beyond pension age and transitions into retirement. This book makes a major contribution and will be essential reading within a range of disciplines, including social gerontology, management, sociology and social policy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aOlder people! Europe! Social conditions. 0aOlder peoplexEmploymentxEconomic aspects. 0aOlder peoplexEmploymentxSocial aspects. 0aOlder peoplexEmploymentzEurope. 0aOlder peoplezEuropexSocial conditions. 70(DE-588)4000571-90(DE-627)1064007110(DE-576)208838643aÄlterer Arbeitnehmer2gnd 70(DE-588)4002737-50(DE-627)1063921660(DE-576)208848517aArbeitsmarktpolitik2gnd 70(DE-588)4035582-20(DE-627)1062469330(DE-576)209013524aLiberalismus2gnd 70(DE-588)4049506-10(DE-627)1061867010(DE-576)209082380aRentenreform2gnd 70(DE-588)4139078-70(DE-627)1056379630(DE-576)209691387aFlexible Altersgrenze2gnd 70(DE-588)4171438-60(DE-627)1053948150(DE-576)209936967aNeoliberalismus2gnd 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Labor.2bisacsh1 aBurnay, Nathalie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGaravaglia, Emma, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHokema, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKrekula, Clary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLain, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLain, David, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov